{"id": "EUVD-2025-27897", "enisaUuid": "ccb144d8-9536-3ee5-ac8b-fe0ff898d867", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: ethernet: ti: am65-cpsw-nuss: Fix skb size by accounting for skb_shared_info\n\nWhile transitioning from netdev_alloc_ip_align() to build_skb(), memory\nfor the \"skb_shared_info\" member of an \"skb\" was not allocated. Fix this\nby allocating \"PAGE_SIZE\" as the skb length, accounting for the packet\nlength, headroom and tailroom, thereby including the required memory space\nfor skb_shared_info.", "datePublished": "2025-08-16T12:30:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T18:32:49", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fc2fffa2facac15ce711e95f98f954426e025bc5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7d6ca0c8c0caf9a13cae2de763bb1f2a9ea7eabb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/02c4d6c26f1f662da8885b299c224ca6628ad232", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38545"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38545"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.0, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "17ec4296-4665-3df4-8463-bab91cbce811", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8acacc40f7337527ff84cd901ed2ef0a2b95b2b6 <fc2fffa2facac15ce711e95f98f954426e025bc5"}, {"id": "387e1584-191a-3599-8a72-41353a38997f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.10"}, {"id": "39503a23-2978-31da-a57c-07045d09caec", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8acacc40f7337527ff84cd901ed2ef0a2b95b2b6 <02c4d6c26f1f662da8885b299c224ca6628ad232"}, {"id": "70a1d871-751f-3509-bed2-778b3a818ced", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "798ccd3a-aee4-39da-b5d4-226bcb79f816", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8acacc40f7337527ff84cd901ed2ef0a2b95b2b6 <7d6ca0c8c0caf9a13cae2de763bb1f2a9ea7eabb"}, {"id": "d2d2eb43-dbd7-3e19-8669-d2b9894d6cdd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.39"}, {"id": "e8885648-4e93-31af-97fb-ff85ef6f61d5", "product": {"name": "Linu